-Return to your seats.
-Sorry.

48:46.166 --> 48:50.375
Oh, God. I don't want to die.

48:50.958 --> 48:52.875
I can't get it to fasten.

48:55.375 --> 48:56.583
Maca, I'm so scared.

48:56.666 --> 48:59.625
How do you think
I'll be remembered if I die here?

48:59.708 --> 49:02.333
I want to be an icon.

49:03.833 --> 49:06.083
Inhale. Exhale.

49:06.166 --> 49:09.166
Maca, you need to record this. Come on.

49:10.958 --> 49:14.916
Let's get my hair a bit messier.
I want it to be kind of shocking.

49:15.833 --> 49:17.500
-How's this?
-Great.

49:17.583 --> 49:20.916
Hi! We're here on a plane,
and it could be going down.

49:21.000 --> 49:23.833
If something happens,
I want you to know that I love you all

49:23.916 --> 49:25.333
and that I'm thinking of you.

49:25.416 --> 49:29.041
And you can upload a video
with the hashtag #WeAreAllPipa.

49:29.125 --> 49:30.583
We are all Pipa!

49:31.750 --> 49:33.416
-Done?
-Yeah.

49:34.625 --> 49:36.291
Oh, this just won't end.

49:38.041 --> 49:39.875
Oh, Maca, I'm so scared.

49:51.250 --> 49:53.416
Unbelievable. What are you doing here?

49:53.500 --> 49:55.708
We're really nose-diving, huh?

49:55.791 --> 49:58.041
You're thinking of me
in your final moments.

49:58.125 --> 50:01.041
Not your parents, Jime,
Adriana, or world peace.

50:01.125 --> 50:02.125
Just me.

50:02.208 --> 50:04.458
Lately, I only think about
how much I hate you.

50:05.458 --> 50:07.791
The fact is, you only think about me.

50:09.041 --> 50:11.125
Is there a last wish I can grant for you?

50:11.208 --> 50:14.333
A kiss? Or, if you want,
we can bang in the bathroom.

50:14.416 --> 50:15.500
It's up to you.

50:38.000 --> 50:39.125
What are you doing?

50:39.208 --> 50:40.416
Maca, open up!

50:44.541 --> 50:45.375
Maca!

50:49.833 --> 50:52.625
Don't give me those looks. He deserves it.

50:55.750 --> 50:57.791
You're so weird lately.

50:58.583 --> 51:00.625
Post my video as soon as we land.

51:08.291 --> 51:09.833
But you landed safely?

51:09.916 --> 51:11.916
Yeah, it was just a scare.

51:12.916 --> 51:16.833
-I think it was an astral journey.
-I think you hyperventilated.

51:16.916 --> 51:18.875
The important thing is I locked him away.

51:18.958 --> 51:20.708
He disappeared.

51:20.791 --> 51:23.708
That's the problem.
You locked him away, but he's still there.

51:23.791 --> 51:28.916
You should've thrown him out of the plane.
What happened the last time you saw him?

51:35.916 --> 51:39.333
It doesn't matter. It was… the last time.

51:41.500 --> 51:42.500
To the last time!

51:42.583 --> 51:44.916
-To the last time!
-To the last time!

51:47.666 --> 51:49.583
What about you guys? What's new?

51:49.666 --> 51:52.166
How about you?
How's life post-threesome?

51:53.500 --> 51:55.208
Fine, but nothing special.

51:55.291 --> 51:56.750
Nothing special? Really?

51:56.833 --> 52:01.500
You try pussy for the first time,
and that's all you say? What the hell?

52:01.583 --> 52:04.291
-I'm not gonna go into details.
-You should!

52:05.291 --> 52:06.250
No.

52:07.041 --> 52:09.500
So, with the hot girl, it was just okay.

52:09.583 --> 52:11.250
But how'd it go with Julián?

52:43.333 --> 52:47.000
I feel like… we're getting the spark back.

52:47.083 --> 52:48.500
We turn each other on.

52:49.166 --> 52:51.458
Messing around was good for us.

52:51.541 --> 52:54.166
Because that's all it was.
Just messing around.

52:54.666 --> 52:56.083
I wouldn't have made that bet.

52:56.166 --> 52:59.791
I really thought you were tired of him,
that it couldn't be fixed.

53:00.708 --> 53:02.625
-Tired of Julián?
-Yeah.

53:03.583 --> 53:06.250
Girls, Julián is my family.

53:06.333 --> 53:09.250
The last thing I want is to leave him.

53:09.333 --> 53:11.208
To throw away the life we've built,

53:11.291 --> 53:14.708
to find a new place to rent,
to take selfies for Tinder…

53:15.750 --> 53:16.708
No, thanks.

53:17.708 --> 53:19.875
How are things
with your physical therapist?

53:20.875 --> 53:21.916
It didn't work out.

53:22.000 --> 53:23.875
-What?
-But you were so good together.

53:23.958 --> 53:24.791
Yeah.

53:25.458 --> 53:28.625
But then something… went seriously wrong.

53:29.125 --> 53:29.958
Jime.

53:31.041 --> 53:33.583
You won't believe
what one of my patients gave me.

53:34.958 --> 53:38.958
Isn't he adorable?
You can name him if you want.

53:41.875 --> 53:46.416
-You ended it because he likes hamsters?
-He really likes them. He's obsessed.

53:46.500 --> 53:49.541
This is the first relationship
you've had that lasted over a month.

53:49.625 --> 53:51.083
And the sex was great.

53:52.125 --> 53:54.375
Yeah, but...

53:55.458 --> 53:58.291
he's so into hamsters.
So into them.

53:59.166 --> 54:01.250
Adri, he obviously wasn't Santi.

54:01.791 --> 54:03.750
I have to keep looking. That's it.

54:06.958 --> 54:08.000
I gotta pee.

54:13.333 --> 54:14.833
She went to cry in there.

54:16.291 --> 54:19.125
And if she keeps this up…
she's gonna die alone.

54:20.083 --> 54:21.000
Or maybe not.

54:29.500 --> 54:31.875
-Good afternoon. Jimena?
-Yes.

54:39.958 --> 54:41.208
Can I come in?

54:42.916 --> 54:43.750
Yeah.

54:49.125 --> 54:51.583
This is more than enough
to get you started.

54:51.666 --> 54:54.541
I'm not sure
I can pretend to be somebody else.

54:54.625 --> 54:56.375
What do you think acting is?

54:56.458 --> 54:58.666
Sharing dog shelter posts
and going gluten-free?

54:59.750 --> 55:02.125
Besides, in your ad,
you said you loved a challenge.

55:02.208 --> 55:06.875
Well, I meant, like,
pretending I'm disabled or Norwegian.

55:06.958 --> 55:09.041
What you're asking for
is straight-up crazy.

55:10.666 --> 55:13.333
Hey, Santi broke his wrist skateboarding
three times.

55:13.416 --> 55:15.458
-Yeah.
-Does that work for you?

55:15.541 --> 55:17.041
Is she really gonna believe this?

55:17.125 --> 55:20.500
Well, Jime's had
a complicated relationship with logic

55:20.583 --> 55:21.750
for the last 11 years.

55:22.458 --> 55:25.583
She'll believe you're Santi.
Then you can say goodbye to her forever.

55:25.666 --> 55:27.708
You'll be setting her free.

55:27.791 --> 55:30.416
And you'll be helping a great cause.

55:31.250 --> 55:33.333
Actors are all about that, right?

55:34.416 --> 55:37.750
Yeah. But what if she asks
about something that isn't in the notes?

55:37.833 --> 55:39.208
You improvise.

55:40.416 --> 55:43.000
Look, as an actor,
this is right in your wheelhouse.

55:43.083 --> 55:46.958
Don't stress about it.
It's just two dates, and then it's over.

55:47.791 --> 55:49.500
So? What's your fee?

55:50.250 --> 55:52.458
Jesus. Man, I hate coconut balls.

55:54.166 --> 55:57.083
It's very important
that you like coconut balls.

55:57.166 --> 55:59.791
Well, it's gonna cost you.

56:02.041 --> 56:03.958
My favorite's the second one.

56:04.041 --> 56:07.958
Well, my favorite's the last one.
I know most people prefer The Two Towers,

56:08.041 --> 56:11.083
but I just watched them,
like, 20 times, so I'm very sure.

56:11.166 --> 56:13.500
And you didn't used to give a crap
about Tolkien?

56:13.583 --> 56:16.166
My tastes have completely changed.
It's crazy.

56:16.250 --> 56:17.375
Since when?

56:18.916 --> 56:21.416
I don't know. Like two months ago.

56:21.500 --> 56:22.500
The salts.

56:22.583 --> 56:25.500
And all of a sudden,
I couldn't get your name out of my head.

56:25.583 --> 56:28.250
"Jime Herrera…"
So, I knew I had to find you.

56:28.333 --> 56:30.375
You must think I'm nuts, right?

56:31.458 --> 56:32.458
Not at all.

56:34.333 --> 56:36.125
What happened to your arm?

56:36.625 --> 56:41.583
Yeah, that. I had this real urge
to hop on a skateboard.

56:41.666 --> 56:45.125
So I bought one and then… triple fracture.
What bad luck, huh?

56:45.916 --> 56:47.500
Can I ask you something?

56:48.000 --> 56:48.875
Sure.

56:48.958 --> 56:51.291
Name a band, a city, a type of cheese,

56:51.375 --> 56:53.916
an animal you hate,
and an episode of The Simpsons.

56:54.708 --> 56:56.166
Wow. Okay.

56:57.416 --> 56:59.833
Let's see. Band? Slipknot.

57:01.625 --> 57:04.333
Edinburgh. Emmentaler.

57:05.333 --> 57:08.166
-The episode with Pinchy.
-A great one!

57:08.250 --> 57:11.291
And… Oh, and rodents. I fucking hate them.

57:21.750 --> 57:23.000
Where've you been hiding?

57:31.291 --> 57:35.791
I FOUND HIM. HE'S SANTI!

57:38.375 --> 57:39.250
Maca.

57:42.750 --> 57:43.583
Maca.

57:49.500 --> 57:51.250
I just wanted to apologize.

57:52.875 --> 57:55.250
For what happened the other day
in my office, and…

57:57.083 --> 57:58.208
for everything.

57:59.583 --> 58:02.000
I left without giving you an explanation.

58:03.000 --> 58:04.208
I was so wrong.

58:04.958 --> 58:05.791
So wrong.

58:06.291 --> 58:10.416
And I'm so sorry because I swear
I never meant to hurt you.

58:17.583 --> 58:19.833
You seemed pretty confident
in your decisions.

58:22.583 --> 58:24.375
No. It was really hard for me

58:24.875 --> 58:28.541
to live my life without you
by my side, bugging me 24/7.

58:31.375 --> 58:32.625
I'm so sorry.

58:35.833 --> 58:37.250
I truly am.

58:43.250 --> 58:44.375
Friends?

58:57.083 --> 58:58.000
Fine.

59:12.916 --> 59:14.166
What are you doing here?

59:15.208 --> 59:16.833
Complicating things for myself.

59:26.500 --> 59:28.750
I made part of the guest list,

59:28.833 --> 59:31.291
and, of course, Raquel had to be invited.

59:31.375 --> 59:35.333
I added a plus-one for her.
But I'm praying she doesn't bring Leo.

59:35.416 --> 59:39.083
Even though he's pretending to be
an adult now, I don't want to see him.

59:40.958 --> 59:41.833
Maca!

59:47.583 --> 59:49.708
Call Mateo. My ponytail's coming undone.

59:49.791 --> 59:51.166
-Want me to fix it?
-No.

59:51.250 --> 59:52.916
-Call Mateo.
-Okay. On it.

59:57.083 --> 59:58.833
Mateo…

59:58.916 --> 59:59.916
Maca!

1:00:00.916 --> 1:00:03.291
-Hey.
-Is this purse yours?

1:00:03.375 --> 1:00:05.500
Pipa gave it to me. It's from Milan.

1:00:05.583 --> 1:00:08.750
She felt bad about the ceremony,
and sometimes she's nice.

1:00:09.458 --> 1:00:12.000
Babe, they gave her
this purse in a showroom.

1:00:12.083 --> 1:00:14.875
She didn't want it
because too many hands had touched it.

1:00:14.958 --> 1:00:15.958
What?

1:00:17.625 --> 1:00:20.625
I could cry from all this stress.

1:00:20.708 --> 1:00:22.583
Don't cry. It's all right.

1:00:25.375 --> 1:00:29.333
Raquel, I'm really sorry for what I said
the other day about Leo.

1:00:30.541 --> 1:00:31.791
It's fine.

1:00:32.291 --> 1:00:35.166
Actually, we're working on
communicating better,

1:00:35.250 --> 1:00:36.666
and it's going well.

1:00:36.750 --> 1:00:39.708
-I'm glad.
-Why don't we all get dinner sometime?

1:00:39.791 --> 1:00:42.958
-No.
-Yeah. It'll be like a new beginning.

1:00:44.958 --> 1:00:46.916
Time to pretend to be an adult.

1:00:48.625 --> 1:00:50.541
-Sure.
-Bring whoever you want.

1:00:51.916 --> 1:00:53.291
I'll let my boyfriend know.

1:00:54.375 --> 1:00:57.125
Anyway, I gotta call Mateo,
Pipa's hairstylist.

1:00:57.208 --> 1:00:58.416
I'll see you later.

1:00:58.500 --> 1:01:00.208
-Okay. See you.
-Bye for now.

1:01:05.875 --> 1:01:08.083
You can't spend your life
running away from him.

1:01:08.166 --> 1:01:10.916
He apologized, you chilled out,
you haven't lost your focus.

1:01:11.000 --> 1:01:12.583
You can be friends.

1:01:12.666 --> 1:01:14.500
Friends? Are you kidding me?

1:01:16.000 --> 1:01:17.333
Now I've heard it all.

1:01:18.541 --> 1:01:20.833
We're gonna be friends with Leo now?

1:01:20.916 --> 1:01:24.125
CRAPPY DECISION

1:01:30.625 --> 1:01:33.875
-You can really throw 'em back, huh?
-Many years of practice.

1:01:33.958 --> 1:01:35.166
I can see that.

1:01:37.000 --> 1:01:41.041
WHY WON'T U RESPOND? ARE YOU MAD AT ME?
DID I DO SOMETHING WRONG?

1:01:41.125 --> 1:01:43.916
Hey, could we go see
an exhibition this Friday?

1:01:44.000 --> 1:01:47.041
There's one at the Reina Sofía
I've been dying to see.

1:01:47.125 --> 1:01:48.250
It's about to close.

1:01:49.166 --> 1:01:53.500
Yeah, I'm not sure.
I was thinking about coming back here.

1:01:53.583 --> 1:01:55.375
-To the skate park?
-Yeah.

1:01:55.458 --> 1:01:58.291
But neither of us can even get on a board.

1:01:59.083 --> 1:02:02.416
Yeah, but I like being here,
hanging out with the guys.

1:02:02.500 --> 1:02:04.083
Santi loved it here.

1:02:04.166 --> 1:02:07.541
And I was planning
to score some weed and get a nice high.

1:02:08.041 --> 1:02:10.333
I don't smoke joints like I used to.

1:02:21.666 --> 1:02:22.500
Maca.

1:02:24.000 --> 1:02:26.041
What are you wearing?

1:02:30.041 --> 1:02:32.791
Remember, we love each other, we're happy,

1:02:32.875 --> 1:02:36.750
we're moving in together,
and you're extremely intelligent.

1:02:36.833 --> 1:02:37.666
Got it.

1:02:38.625 --> 1:02:42.291
We're looking for something
around La Latina or Barrio de Letras.

1:02:42.375 --> 1:02:44.083
I love those areas.

1:02:44.166 --> 1:02:47.500
But we were thinking about
moving out of the city, right?

1:02:47.583 --> 1:02:49.041
-Yeah.
-To the country?

1:02:49.125 --> 1:02:52.208
But Leo puts on bug spray
anytime he goes past the M-30.

1:02:53.208 --> 1:02:56.625
Then it's about time
he gets in touch with nature.

1:02:56.708 --> 1:02:59.250
-Reconnect with Pachamama.
-Pachamama.

1:02:59.333 --> 1:03:03.458
The truth is, the air quality
in the city has been awful lately.

1:03:03.541 --> 1:03:05.958
But if you're going to live in La Latina…

1:03:06.041 --> 1:03:07.041
Thank you.

1:03:08.000 --> 1:03:10.291
Whatever my baby wants.

1:03:15.541 --> 1:03:19.708
Coque, what is it you do, exactly?
Aside from getting very nice tattoos.

1:03:19.791 --> 1:03:23.916
Thanks. Well, I do a bit of everything.
I DJ. I do podcasts, stand-up…

1:03:24.000 --> 1:03:25.125
-Stand-up?
-Yeah.

1:03:25.208 --> 1:03:27.416
Rent prices must've gone down
in the city, huh?

1:03:28.375 --> 1:03:29.833
And what's your stand-up about?

1:03:29.916 --> 1:03:33.291
-How are the urban gardens doing?
-Wait, don't tell me.

1:03:33.375 --> 1:03:36.500
-Millennial sexcapades?
-You've seen my stuff!

1:03:37.291 --> 1:03:39.041
It's cool you do so many things, Coque.

1:03:39.625 --> 1:03:42.833
And they say there are no entrepreneurs
in this country. A toast.

1:03:42.916 --> 1:03:44.250
You sound like an old man.

1:03:45.333 --> 1:03:47.083
I kind of am one. In spirit.

1:03:47.166 --> 1:03:51.083
Yeah. How old were you when you started
wearing a robe around the house? Ten?

1:03:51.166 --> 1:03:54.541
That's a bit much. That's really too much.

1:03:55.041 --> 1:03:57.958
-I bet you still wear it.
-Know what's too much?

1:03:58.041 --> 1:04:02.375
Nobody knows where that robe went.
It mysteriously disappeared.

1:04:03.791 --> 1:04:05.583
You can fess up to it. It's been years.

1:04:05.666 --> 1:04:06.666
-No.
-Where is it?

1:04:06.750 --> 1:04:09.666
I don't know.
It must've wound up in the same place as…

1:04:10.833 --> 1:04:11.833
As what?

1:04:13.083 --> 1:04:14.416
The same place…

1:04:14.500 --> 1:04:16.875
-Yeah.
-I totally forgot about it! For real?

1:04:16.958 --> 1:04:18.791
-No, not there.
-In the same place?

1:04:18.875 --> 1:04:20.916
Yeah.

1:04:21.625 --> 1:04:22.666
-No.
-Yes.

1:04:22.750 --> 1:04:24.916
Do you know why I thought that?

1:04:25.000 --> 1:04:28.708
Remember that time
your mom brought us lasagna?

1:04:28.791 --> 1:04:32.375
We're really interested
in urban gardens, Raquel.

1:04:32.458 --> 1:04:35.708
Because we want an apartment
with a balcony.

1:04:35.791 --> 1:04:37.458
That's important. A balcony.

1:04:40.916 --> 1:04:42.333
I don't know.

1:04:42.916 --> 1:04:46.083
-He's not how I imagined.
-You can't judge a book by its cover.

1:04:46.166 --> 1:04:48.208
-Right.
-Raquel really liked him.

1:04:48.291 --> 1:04:50.625
That's because Raquel
is great with everyone.

1:04:52.083 --> 1:04:54.541
-You're really moving in together?
-Why wouldn't we be?

1:04:54.625 --> 1:04:58.958
I don't know, Maca.
I just can't picture you two together.

1:05:00.208 --> 1:05:01.666
And who can you picture me with?

1:05:04.916 --> 1:05:07.791
How interesting. Well, let us know.

1:05:07.875 --> 1:05:09.041
Hey.

1:05:09.541 --> 1:05:11.416
-Should we get going?
-Yeah.

1:05:11.500 --> 1:05:14.000
-Let's do this again sometime.
-Yeah.

1:05:14.083 --> 1:05:15.125
-Soon?
-Soon.

1:05:15.208 --> 1:05:16.458
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

1:05:17.208 --> 1:05:18.625
-Bye.
-Bye.

1:05:19.291 --> 1:05:21.833
-That went awesome, huh?
-How about a drink?

1:05:27.208 --> 1:05:31.458
Hey, Adri. Are you free for lunch?
I don't know what to do. I mean…

1:05:31.541 --> 1:05:35.208
I need to talk,
and you're the group's voice of reason.

1:05:35.291 --> 1:05:38.083
I'll drop by your shop
at noon, okay?

1:06:02.291 --> 1:06:03.166
You cutie.

1:06:09.750 --> 1:06:10.833
Maca!

1:06:14.666 --> 1:06:15.916
You look amazing.

1:06:16.625 --> 1:06:19.166
Before you leave,
organize my bags too, okay?

1:06:19.250 --> 1:06:20.583
I gotta go. I have plans.

1:06:20.666 --> 1:06:22.833
If you hurry,
you'll finish before eight today.

1:06:23.708 --> 1:06:26.166
-Okay. Have a good time.
-Thanks, sweetie.

1:06:32.458 --> 1:06:37.708
MACA, I'M PASSING YOUR CV AROUND.
I'LL KEEP YOU POSTED.

1:06:45.125 --> 1:06:45.958
Hi.

1:06:47.541 --> 1:06:50.916
-How did you know where I work?
-I asked around.

1:06:52.375 --> 1:06:53.541
Wow.

1:06:53.625 --> 1:06:54.875
Sorry.

1:06:55.625 --> 1:06:58.000
He can't stop with the apologies lately.

1:06:58.875 --> 1:07:00.166
It suits him.

1:07:00.916 --> 1:07:03.833
-Let me take you to dinner.
-Is Raquel joining us?

1:07:04.541 --> 1:07:06.333
As in, "I want her to come."

1:07:06.416 --> 1:07:09.666
No. The thing is,
I'm writing a research paper

1:07:09.750 --> 1:07:15.166
on love in contemporary literature,
and… I'd really like to hear your opinion.

1:07:17.208 --> 1:07:18.541
Something quick.

1:07:18.625 --> 1:07:20.416
-Not a sit-down thing, okay?
-All right.

1:07:24.500 --> 1:07:28.458
I like it overall, but… I don't know.
It's missing something.

1:07:28.541 --> 1:07:29.458
Something like?

1:07:30.083 --> 1:07:32.958
It needs to be more emotionally involved.

1:07:33.458 --> 1:07:37.833
It's just theory. You analyze
these stories, but it's detached.

1:07:37.916 --> 1:07:40.125
I see. So?

1:07:41.375 --> 1:07:45.125
Take a look around you,
not just at the pages in a book.

1:07:45.958 --> 1:07:47.083
Around me?

1:07:48.166 --> 1:07:50.791
Yeah. At the people who are close to you.

1:07:51.291 --> 1:07:53.958
Your memories. Your experiences.

1:07:55.458 --> 1:07:59.333
You know reflecting on my own life
isn't my strong suit.

1:08:02.083 --> 1:08:03.375
Are you hungry?

1:08:04.208 --> 1:08:06.125
She isn't texting me back either.

1:08:07.125 --> 1:08:09.375
Pipa must have her slaving away again.

1:08:09.875 --> 1:08:12.958
-Definitely.
-So, how are you doing?

1:08:14.291 --> 1:08:15.416
Just great.

1:08:16.208 --> 1:08:18.125
Well, great

1:08:18.625 --> 1:08:21.750
or more than great.
Or more than, more than great.

1:08:21.833 --> 1:08:22.833
Really?

1:08:22.916 --> 1:08:24.958
Well, Santi Part Two is…

1:08:26.666 --> 1:08:29.125
I don't know. I can't even explain it.

1:08:29.791 --> 1:08:32.208
Oh, but… You're still seeing him?

1:08:32.291 --> 1:08:37.125
Of course. I spent years looking for him.
Now I gotta face the consequences.

1:08:41.333 --> 1:08:45.958
JORGE, YOU HAVEN'T BROKEN UP WITH HER YET?

1:08:48.333 --> 1:08:49.833
WHY?

1:08:49.916 --> 1:08:52.041
I LOVE HER!

1:08:52.541 --> 1:08:55.125
He's my man. Just like Julián's yours.

1:09:01.250 --> 1:09:02.875
-Jime…
-What?

1:09:06.291 --> 1:09:09.208
I get a 50% discount on wedding dresses.

1:09:10.708 --> 1:09:12.250
-Interested?
-Great plan!

1:09:12.333 --> 1:09:15.041
-Right?
-And in three months, a huge wedding!

1:09:15.125 --> 1:09:17.000
Come on. Let's get going.

1:09:18.083 --> 1:09:19.208
Crap.

1:09:25.458 --> 1:09:27.250
-It's weird.
-What is?

1:09:28.041 --> 1:09:30.500
You're the same guy,
but you're so different.

1:09:30.583 --> 1:09:31.708
How?

1:09:33.708 --> 1:09:35.958
I guess you seem more grown-up.

1:09:37.750 --> 1:09:40.916
I get the feeling
things would be different now.

1:09:43.375 --> 1:09:45.541
Don't get me wrong.
I'm not suggesting anything.

1:09:45.625 --> 1:09:46.833
No, of course not.

1:09:48.000 --> 1:09:53.041
It's just, Raquel looks so happy,
and you look so at peace,

1:09:53.125 --> 1:09:55.541
and our relationship
was so different from that.

1:09:56.750 --> 1:09:59.833
Maca, we were very happy too.

1:10:01.041 --> 1:10:03.000
What we had was really special.

1:10:04.083 --> 1:10:07.166
Maybe I'm just talking for myself here,
but I have great memories.

1:10:07.250 --> 1:10:08.291
Sure.

1:10:11.708 --> 1:10:16.083
I need you to think about what we had
as a great period in our lives, Maca.

1:10:16.166 --> 1:10:20.166
It's true we had our share
of hard times too, but it was great.

1:10:21.083 --> 1:10:23.625
And it helped us become who we are today.

1:10:24.625 --> 1:10:26.250
I don't know who I am.

1:10:28.625 --> 1:10:30.625
You're an amazing woman.

1:10:32.208 --> 1:10:33.833
And a robe thief.

1:10:34.541 --> 1:10:35.791
You're stubborn.

1:10:37.083 --> 1:10:39.583
You're capable of inciting a student riot.

1:10:41.666 --> 1:10:44.125
You're someone with dazzling eyes.

1:10:47.541 --> 1:10:49.416
But most of all, you're stubborn.

1:11:17.750 --> 1:11:18.875
Check out this house.

1:11:18.958 --> 1:11:22.666
A water recycling system,
a vegetable garden, solar panels.

1:11:23.166 --> 1:11:24.458
I love it.

1:11:30.333 --> 1:11:32.708
Jime, I need to tell you something.

1:11:32.791 --> 1:11:34.708
It's a message from Santi.

1:11:37.458 --> 1:11:39.500
Jime, I'm getting something.

1:11:39.583 --> 1:11:41.750
-From Santi?
-Yeah.

1:11:43.458 --> 1:11:44.916
I'm getting that…

1:11:48.000 --> 1:11:50.583
you're amazing
and I really like spending time with you.

1:11:52.458 --> 1:11:54.833
I mean, we get each other, right?

1:11:54.916 --> 1:11:56.958
-We laugh together.
-Yeah.

1:11:57.458 --> 1:12:00.958
Santi and I connected the most
over our sense of humor.

1:12:01.041 --> 1:12:03.916
-I'm funny too, right?
-Yeah.

1:12:09.208 --> 1:12:10.333
Check this out.

1:12:11.000 --> 1:12:13.541
"For it shows things that were,
and things that are,

1:12:13.625 --> 1:12:16.833
things that yet may be.
But which it is that he sees…"

1:12:16.916 --> 1:12:19.291
"Even the wisest cannot always tell."

1:12:19.375 --> 1:12:21.291
-The Lord of the Rings?
-Yeah.

1:12:31.500 --> 1:12:34.291
-I'm really happy with you.
-So am I.

1:12:37.041 --> 1:12:40.000
-But you can't keep doing this, Adri.
-I know.

1:12:41.000 --> 1:12:42.583
I think about it every day.

1:12:46.000 --> 1:12:47.000
I know.

1:12:56.583 --> 1:12:57.791
I gotta go.

1:13:06.000 --> 1:13:06.833
Hey.

1:13:07.541 --> 1:13:08.500
Hey.

1:13:10.000 --> 1:13:11.333
It's not your fault.

1:13:12.208 --> 1:13:14.416
What I had with Raquel
wasn't going anywhere.

1:13:15.833 --> 1:13:17.458
It's not your fault, but

1:13:18.791 --> 1:13:21.791
since I saw you, I haven't been able
to stop thinking about you.

1:13:24.375 --> 1:13:26.125
If this were a rom-com,

1:13:26.208 --> 1:13:29.000
a torrential downpour
would start right about now.

1:13:33.708 --> 1:13:37.500
Maca, I'm sorry. This wasn't my plan.

1:13:37.583 --> 1:13:39.750
I know you still resent me
and I deserve it…

1:13:39.833 --> 1:13:41.708
because I've been an idiot.

1:13:42.875 --> 1:13:45.750
If you'd been the one to leave,
I would've been crushed.

1:13:46.916 --> 1:13:48.833
You're right. I'm a dick.

1:13:49.583 --> 1:13:52.000
I'm a conceited jerk
who ruins someone's life

1:13:52.083 --> 1:13:54.333
and doesn't even have the balls
to apologize.

1:13:54.416 --> 1:13:57.875
And, I'll admit,
it hurts to see you with somebody else

1:13:58.375 --> 1:13:59.500
because I love you.

1:14:00.166 --> 1:14:01.083
I love you.

1:14:02.541 --> 1:14:08.291
Okay, now if this really were a rom-com,
I would've leaped into his arms.

1:14:10.000 --> 1:14:11.750
I exist only when you look at me.

1:14:11.833 --> 1:14:13.791
-Don't say that.
-It's the truth.

1:14:13.875 --> 1:14:15.875
Even when I'm not looking,
you exist.

1:14:16.375 --> 1:14:19.750
See? You're still exist, right?

1:18:57.958 --> 1:18:58.791
Hey.

1:19:01.208 --> 1:19:03.041
Want… milk?

1:19:08.166 --> 1:19:09.000
Sure.

1:19:09.708 --> 1:19:11.833
-Is this coffee?
-No.

1:19:12.750 --> 1:19:14.416
-Milk?
-Just milk.

1:19:14.500 --> 1:19:15.791
Just milk? Okay.

1:19:15.875 --> 1:19:18.125
This is… Okay. All right.

1:19:18.625 --> 1:19:21.166
-Here, in the Clarín one?
-Whichever one you want.

1:19:21.250 --> 1:19:22.625
-Okay.
-Yeah.

1:19:26.125 --> 1:19:27.750
Your clothespin looks nice.

1:19:31.708 --> 1:19:34.000
Welcome to Pipa's world.

1:19:34.083 --> 1:19:37.291
So, we finally get
to see the beast's lair.

1:19:40.416 --> 1:19:42.833
-This is where you work, Maca?
-Yeah.

1:19:45.125 --> 1:19:47.333
This is unbelievable.

1:19:49.208 --> 1:19:52.791
-You're sure she's not gonna show up?
-Yeah. She's in Ibiza this weekend.

1:19:52.875 --> 1:19:56.000
-I can't believe this!
-It'd be cool if she never came back.

1:19:56.625 --> 1:19:59.625
-Remember, she's the one who pays me.
-Yeah, I know.

1:19:59.708 --> 1:20:03.541
At her age, I still lived with my folks
and had no plans to move out.

1:20:03.625 --> 1:20:05.833
-Hi, girls.
-Hi.

1:20:07.916 --> 1:20:09.291
What's this?

1:20:10.000 --> 1:20:13.500
-For fanning your ego?
-Oh, please do. Just a bit.

1:20:14.333 --> 1:20:16.875
Careful. It'd take Maca
six months to pay that off.

1:20:17.375 --> 1:20:19.000
This is insane.

1:20:23.333 --> 1:20:27.875
Hey, how are you? I'm a millionaire,
and I get paid for posting on Instagram.

1:20:29.541 --> 1:20:32.333
Adri, do I look like her?

1:20:34.875 --> 1:20:39.291
-Not bad. Give me a bit more vanity.
-Yeah, I also need that tribal look.

1:20:42.500 --> 1:20:44.000
And here's the best part.

1:20:45.166 --> 1:20:49.083
-Help yourselves, ladies.
-Wait. We can try on anything we want?

1:20:49.166 --> 1:20:50.666
-Yeah.
-That's crazy.

1:20:50.750 --> 1:20:54.958
Take whatever you like from this pile.
They're gifts she hasn't opened.

1:20:55.041 --> 1:20:55.916
I'm gonna cry.

1:20:56.541 --> 1:20:59.125
-Oh là là, comment ça va ?
-Mon chéri.

1:21:00.375 --> 1:21:05.000
Maca. Oh, Maca, don't eat, okay? Maca.

1:21:05.083 --> 1:21:07.083
Maca, don't breathe.

1:21:07.875 --> 1:21:10.708
I don't get why I haven't reached
ten million followers yet.

1:21:10.791 --> 1:21:12.833
It's all your fault, Maca.

1:21:14.875 --> 1:21:18.000
Sweetie, you know
I want you to wear heels.

1:21:18.083 --> 1:21:19.875
It looks better.

1:21:24.583 --> 1:21:25.416
Goodbye.

1:22:07.916 --> 1:22:09.000
Here's to us.

1:22:09.083 --> 1:22:11.250
And to getting wasted tonight.

1:22:12.916 --> 1:22:13.750
Cheers.

1:22:13.833 --> 1:22:17.958
Wow, Adri. You are smoking hot
in that dress. I can't believe it.

1:22:18.041 --> 1:22:19.125
-Totally.
-Yeah?

1:22:19.208 --> 1:22:20.041
Keep it.

1:22:20.541 --> 1:22:22.291
-What?
-For real. It's yours.

1:22:22.375 --> 1:22:23.583
Seriously?

1:22:24.333 --> 1:22:27.416
I'll only be able
to squeeze into it for so long…

1:22:27.500 --> 1:22:29.708
Don't start with those insecurities now.

1:22:29.791 --> 1:22:32.708
Girls, there's something
I have to tell you.

1:22:33.958 --> 1:22:37.375
You already know that…
well, that my life needed a change.

1:22:38.208 --> 1:22:41.208
Listen, Adri,
what matters most is accepting it.

1:22:41.291 --> 1:22:44.208
Don't worry,
we won't have any issues with it.

1:22:44.291 --> 1:22:45.291
What's up?

1:22:46.208 --> 1:22:48.916
Julián and I have decided
to take the next step.

1:22:51.416 --> 1:22:55.083
We're gonna try for a baby.
We want a baby!

1:22:55.583 --> 1:22:58.541
-I'm gonna be an aunt?
-Maybe even a godmother.

1:22:58.625 --> 1:22:59.708
What? Oh my God!

1:23:01.791 --> 1:23:04.125
Well, we've got to celebrate, right?

1:23:04.208 --> 1:23:07.208
For sure. Somewhere
that's as great as this news is.

1:23:07.291 --> 1:23:09.500
-Yes, please.
-I know this awesome rooftop bar.

1:23:09.583 --> 1:23:11.791
-Let's go.
-It has a pool. You'll love it.

1:23:13.041 --> 1:23:16.000
Hey. Head downstairs,
and I'll catch up with you.

1:23:16.083 --> 1:23:17.166
-Okay.
-Okay.

1:23:19.666 --> 1:23:20.625
Hello?

1:23:20.708 --> 1:23:22.666
Bonsoir. Macarena Bartual?

1:23:22.750 --> 1:23:25.791
-Yes, this is Macarena.
-I'm calling from Good Mode Magazine.

1:23:25.875 --> 1:23:28.375
I'm Clément Dubois, the magazine's editor.

1:23:28.458 --> 1:23:30.375
Yes? Hello, good evening.

1:23:30.458 --> 1:23:33.208
-I assume you've heard of Good Mode.
-Yes.

1:23:33.291 --> 1:23:36.750
Raquel sent us your CV
and a glowing recommendation.

1:23:36.833 --> 1:23:39.583
I must say, we really like your profile.

1:23:39.666 --> 1:23:40.500
That's great.

1:23:40.583 --> 1:23:44.583
We need someone to manage
the magazine's new media strategy,

1:23:44.666 --> 1:23:48.458
someone with experience in social media,
and we thought of you.

1:23:48.541 --> 1:23:53.208
-Would you be interested?
-Thank you so much. You won't regret it.

1:23:53.291 --> 1:23:56.041
I'll give it my all.

1:23:56.125 --> 1:23:59.000
You'd be joining
our communications department.

1:23:59.083 --> 1:24:03.000
But the position's based
in our Paris headquarters, not in Madrid.

1:24:03.083 --> 1:24:06.875
-Have you ever been to Paris?
-Paris? Yes.

1:24:07.791 --> 1:24:09.416
I love you a lot.

1:24:09.500 --> 1:24:15.333
I love Paris. The Eiffel Tower,
pain au chocolat, croissants.

1:24:15.416 --> 1:24:18.000
Super. We'd need you to start right away.

1:24:18.083 --> 1:24:20.625
If you could give us an answer
in two weeks…

1:24:20.708 --> 1:24:23.125
Two weeks. Oui.

1:24:23.208 --> 1:24:26.333
Or earlier if you want.
Merci beaucoup, Macarena.

1:24:26.416 --> 1:24:28.666
-Merci, au revoir.
-Merci, au revoir.

1:25:26.500 --> 1:25:30.041
I love you guys so much.
We'll always be together, right?

1:25:30.125 --> 1:25:32.666
-Always.
-Always.

1:25:36.333 --> 1:25:38.291
Damn, you guys are the best.

1:25:43.208 --> 1:25:44.291
I love Leo.

1:25:45.000 --> 1:25:46.250
I love Leo!

1:25:47.333 --> 1:25:49.791
I love him.

1:25:49.875 --> 1:25:53.833
When I'm with him, it's like…

1:25:53.916 --> 1:25:57.000
It's hard to put into words.

1:25:57.083 --> 1:25:59.208
My head just explodes.

1:25:59.291 --> 1:26:01.041
My heart too.

1:26:01.750 --> 1:26:04.500
I think she's traveling back in time.

1:26:04.583 --> 1:26:07.750
Maca, what year are you in?

1:26:07.833 --> 1:26:11.791
Do they still have MP3 players?
Do cell phones have keyboards?

1:26:11.875 --> 1:26:13.875
What do you got there, Snake?

1:26:17.041 --> 1:26:19.541
-What?
-Maca, did you see him again?

1:26:21.000 --> 1:26:22.708
After what he did to you?

1:26:22.791 --> 1:26:26.041
Didn't you lock him in the plane bathroom?
What happened? He escaped?

1:26:26.125 --> 1:26:29.666
I didn't want to.
Well, no, I did. He smells so good.

1:26:29.750 --> 1:26:32.666
But I haven't forgotten
what he did to me. No.

1:26:32.750 --> 1:26:35.791
Maca, look.
Weren't you trying to become empowered?

1:26:35.875 --> 1:26:37.375
What the hell do I know?

1:26:37.458 --> 1:26:39.041
-All right, that's it.
-No.

1:26:39.125 --> 1:26:41.166
-I'm changing the song.
-Adriana.

1:26:41.250 --> 1:26:42.541
Adriana!

1:26:42.625 --> 1:26:45.750
Hey. He left you a total wreck.
He's your kryptonite.

1:26:45.833 --> 1:26:46.666
Maca!

1:26:46.750 --> 1:26:49.416
You ditched us for him.
We talked about this.

1:26:49.500 --> 1:26:52.916
I get it now.
That's why you let Pipa walk all over you.

1:26:53.000 --> 1:26:56.250
Because when he shows up,
you don't give a damn about anything else.

1:26:56.333 --> 1:26:59.291
You need to stop this. Now. Right now.

1:26:59.375 --> 1:27:02.000
I know what's good for me,
and I do the opposite. So what?

1:27:02.083 --> 1:27:04.625
Just like how you're hung up
on the threesome girl,

1:27:04.708 --> 1:27:08.333
and you still want a kid with Julián,
who you haven't cared about in years.

1:27:08.416 --> 1:27:10.708
You fell for the girl from the threesome?

1:27:12.041 --> 1:27:12.916
I saw you together.

1:27:16.166 --> 1:27:19.625
-Fuck you.
-I saw you. I'd never seen you that happy.

1:27:19.708 --> 1:27:23.000
You were beaming.
And now you're having a kid with Julián?

1:27:23.083 --> 1:27:25.291
I don't know if things
will work out with Julia.

1:27:25.375 --> 1:27:27.208
It's not that simple, you know?

1:27:27.750 --> 1:27:31.791
Are you really going to settle
out of fear of being alone? Take a risk!

1:27:32.458 --> 1:27:36.625
Says the one hiding behind
her first boyfriend to avoid moving on.

1:27:40.083 --> 1:27:42.708
Okay, anything else
to confess, you vipers?

1:27:42.791 --> 1:27:44.583
Yeah. Santi's dead!

1:28:01.333 --> 1:28:02.166
That's right.

1:28:03.125 --> 1:28:05.416
We all have our kryptonite.

1:28:05.875 --> 1:28:08.958
And it seems easier
to keep it locked away than to face it.

1:28:10.458 --> 1:28:14.541
That night, the three of us decided
to run from our uncomfortable truths

1:28:14.625 --> 1:28:16.708
by seeking shelter at home.

1:28:22.833 --> 1:28:24.541
How'd it go with the girls?

1:28:25.833 --> 1:28:26.750
Good.

1:28:31.666 --> 1:28:33.208
We have to do it today, right?

1:28:34.708 --> 1:28:37.458
Wake me up early,
and we'll have a quickie.

1:28:44.208 --> 1:28:49.291
Hey. What's wrong?
You scared me when you said it was urgent.

1:28:50.541 --> 1:28:51.500
Are you okay?

1:28:57.500 --> 1:28:58.750
Wanna get married?

1:29:25.916 --> 1:29:27.125
Bonjour. Clément?

1:29:28.875 --> 1:29:31.875
Yes, but I still have
three days to decide, right?

1:29:32.375 --> 1:29:36.666
Okay. I'll let you know on Monday.
I'm still wrapping up a few things.

1:29:37.166 --> 1:29:38.333
Yes.

1:29:38.416 --> 1:29:40.041
Merci. Merci beaucoup.

1:29:53.166 --> 1:29:57.083
After all, I'm not that bad off here.
Check this place out.

1:29:57.166 --> 1:30:00.083
Maca!

1:30:00.166 --> 1:30:04.583
Where did you put my eggplant belt?
Oh, why can't I ever find anything?

1:30:05.083 --> 1:30:06.291
Coming!

1:30:15.791 --> 1:30:18.125
I got a job offer.

1:30:18.208 --> 1:30:21.208
It's a position at a really good magazine.

1:30:21.708 --> 1:30:22.958
Really?

1:30:23.041 --> 1:30:24.541
It's a great opportunity.

1:30:25.375 --> 1:30:27.291
You're so talented, Macarena.

1:30:27.375 --> 1:30:29.791
-Yeah, but--
-The Pipa thing's a dead end.

1:30:30.291 --> 1:30:32.041
But the thing is…

1:30:32.125 --> 1:30:33.958
I am so proud of you.

1:30:40.083 --> 1:30:41.208
I love you.

1:30:42.250 --> 1:30:43.500
I love you too.

1:30:51.666 --> 1:30:53.791
I want to be

1:30:54.541 --> 1:30:56.833
Whatever I want to be

1:30:57.333 --> 1:30:59.333
I love myself

1:31:00.625 --> 1:31:04.291
I love myself

1:31:04.875 --> 1:31:08.000
I want to see you free
I want to see you strong

1:31:08.083 --> 1:31:12.416
I want to see you whole

1:31:19.333 --> 1:31:23.916
Whole

1:31:27.958 --> 1:31:30.791
And if we lost each other

1:31:31.416 --> 1:31:34.958
We'll meet again

1:31:39.791 --> 1:31:41.125
Far away

1:31:41.208 --> 1:31:44.500
And if we meet

1:31:44.583 --> 1:31:48.541
We'll have the clarity to see

1:31:49.583 --> 1:31:52.166
What's coming our way

1:31:52.250 --> 1:31:59.208
Accept and comprehend
That everything can end

1:31:59.291 --> 1:32:01.416
Whole

1:32:08.375 --> 1:32:11.375
Whole

1:32:12.375 --> 1:32:13.208
Hi.

1:32:13.708 --> 1:32:17.458
Hi, babe.
I got you folic acid. It's in the kitchen.

1:32:17.541 --> 1:32:21.250
I asked about paternity leave at work,
and it won't be an issue.

1:32:21.333 --> 1:32:24.500
You'll see. We've got this.

1:32:29.208 --> 1:32:30.041
What's wrong?

1:32:31.500 --> 1:32:32.416
Jime.

1:32:33.250 --> 1:32:38.041
We're moving really fast, and I have
something important to tell you.

1:32:38.833 --> 1:32:41.583
How about we see if this can work
without the spirit thing?

1:32:42.166 --> 1:32:43.125
What?

1:32:45.916 --> 1:32:47.375
I'm not Santi.

1:32:48.583 --> 1:32:52.541
Your friends hired me to pretend
to be him and say goodbye to you.

1:32:52.625 --> 1:32:54.500
So you'd finally be free.

1:32:54.583 --> 1:32:56.625
But then I started
having feelings for you.

1:32:56.708 --> 1:32:59.083
I'm sorry. I didn't want to lie to you.

1:32:59.166 --> 1:33:01.541
I'm an idiot. That's it. I said it.

1:33:01.625 --> 1:33:03.875
And they told you what he liked?

1:33:04.916 --> 1:33:06.666
What bitches, right?

1:33:06.750 --> 1:33:09.250
I fucking hate coconut balls and elves.

1:33:09.916 --> 1:33:10.916
I do too.

1:33:14.125 --> 1:33:15.208
I swear.

1:33:15.833 --> 1:33:17.500
And this is a fake cast.

1:33:18.000 --> 1:33:20.625
I can't wait to take this shit off.

1:33:20.708 --> 1:33:22.666
Damn. So, you're an actor?

1:33:22.750 --> 1:33:24.166
Yeah, that part's true.

1:33:27.416 --> 1:33:28.333
Hey.

1:33:29.500 --> 1:33:30.875
I really like you.

1:33:31.375 --> 1:33:33.875
Do you still wanna get married?

1:33:35.666 --> 1:33:39.708
I really like you too,
but I think we're better off as friends.

1:33:39.791 --> 1:33:42.208
It's just… Look, I need to go.

1:33:42.291 --> 1:33:45.666
But if you want to be friends,
I'm all for that, okay?

1:33:46.875 --> 1:33:49.041
I don't know. Call me if you want,

1:33:49.125 --> 1:33:52.250
and I'll get back to you,
and we'll be in touch.

1:33:53.458 --> 1:33:55.375
I dunno. We'll see what happens.

1:33:57.583 --> 1:34:00.916
I have to take care of
something really important. Sor--

1:34:02.291 --> 1:34:03.208
I'm okay!

1:34:05.083 --> 1:34:06.166
Bye!

1:34:09.916 --> 1:34:11.958
Jimena, Samuel's seeing a patient.

1:34:25.125 --> 1:34:27.083
It's okay, Victoria. Relax.

1:34:34.916 --> 1:34:37.875
Relax. It's nothing.
Want me to put on some music?

1:34:47.583 --> 1:34:50.375
DRINKS?

1:35:32.250 --> 1:35:36.208
Two more steps forward and step up.
Perfect. There you go.

1:35:38.000 --> 1:35:40.916
There. Hold on. I'll close the door.

1:35:42.291 --> 1:35:43.708
Now, straight ahead.

1:35:46.375 --> 1:35:47.666
There. Great.

1:35:49.208 --> 1:35:51.750
Wait. Now turn to the right a bit.

1:35:53.708 --> 1:35:55.291
A little further.

1:35:55.791 --> 1:35:57.041
A little more.

1:35:57.541 --> 1:35:58.500
Here.

1:35:58.583 --> 1:36:00.458
-Ready?
-Yeah.

1:36:13.791 --> 1:36:15.250
It looks the same.

1:36:19.541 --> 1:36:21.875
But… what're we doing here?

1:36:26.000 --> 1:36:27.125
Remember this?

1:36:30.458 --> 1:36:35.041
-The photo from my pool membership card.
-You got it taken on our second date.

1:36:35.125 --> 1:36:37.250
-Remember?
-Yeah.

1:36:37.750 --> 1:36:39.375
I've kept it with me.

1:36:40.916 --> 1:36:43.291
Because I never stopped loving you, Maca.

1:36:44.416 --> 1:36:46.208
And this time, I'm not letting you go.

1:36:47.041 --> 1:36:48.541
I know you so well…

1:36:50.958 --> 1:36:53.500
but at the same time,
it's like we just met.

1:36:54.541 --> 1:36:55.500
Maca…

1:36:58.458 --> 1:37:00.958
I want us to live here together.

1:37:02.958 --> 1:37:05.208
I want to wake up beside you every day.

1:37:07.666 --> 1:37:08.750
And I want…

1:37:10.291 --> 1:37:13.375
to eat breakfast with you
on this balcony every morning.

1:37:17.541 --> 1:37:20.333
We'll eat breakfast
on that balcony every morning.

1:37:23.541 --> 1:37:27.541
-Look at all this natural light.
-It's so nice. I love it.

1:37:29.666 --> 1:37:32.041
Oh, and we can use this room as a study.

1:37:32.625 --> 1:37:37.291
Money might be a little tight at first,
but it'll be worth it, won't it?

1:37:38.416 --> 1:37:41.958
-Should we do it, then?
-You'd applied for a scholarship.

1:37:42.041 --> 1:37:45.416
You were afraid to commit.
You know it. What're you doing?

1:37:45.500 --> 1:37:48.166
-I'm gonna tell them we'll take it.
-Okay.

1:37:49.458 --> 1:37:50.666
What are you doing?

1:37:51.875 --> 1:37:53.875
I can't stand you.

1:37:55.250 --> 1:37:57.916
Well, your past self
doesn't seem so upset.

1:37:59.875 --> 1:38:01.041
Why, Leo?

1:38:01.958 --> 1:38:04.250
Why don't you say it
when I get off that call?

1:38:05.875 --> 1:38:08.041
Why don't you tell me
about the scholarship?

1:38:08.125 --> 1:38:10.291
We could've gone there together.

1:38:11.750 --> 1:38:14.583
If I go, it doesn't mean
I'm not madly in love with you.

1:38:14.666 --> 1:38:17.458
I'm asking why
you can't be honest with me.

1:38:23.333 --> 1:38:24.458
Because I'm afraid.

1:38:25.583 --> 1:38:28.541
-Afraid of what?
-I don't know. Of losing it all.

1:38:33.791 --> 1:38:36.041
You think I'll get the scholarship?

1:38:44.333 --> 1:38:46.250
You needed to go by yourself.

1:38:47.708 --> 1:38:48.833
That's why.

1:38:50.166 --> 1:38:52.666
That's what you couldn't say to my face.

1:38:57.625 --> 1:38:59.250
Now I get it, Leo.

1:39:02.166 --> 1:39:04.208
She wasn't able to understand, but I am.

1:39:05.166 --> 1:39:07.833
We're the couple
who's looking at the apartment.

1:39:08.333 --> 1:39:10.208
-Tell her.
-It's great.

1:39:12.041 --> 1:39:13.791
Can't you see how excited she is?

1:39:13.875 --> 1:39:15.666
We love the apartment, and…

1:39:15.750 --> 1:39:18.041
You're going to break her heart.

1:39:21.583 --> 1:39:22.708
Okay. Tomorrow…

1:39:22.791 --> 1:39:23.666
Tell her.

1:39:23.750 --> 1:39:25.833
…we'll get the information to you…

1:39:25.916 --> 1:39:28.166
Thanks so much. That's so nice of you.

1:39:42.000 --> 1:39:43.375
I'm so happy.

1:39:57.708 --> 1:40:00.458
I got a job offer in Paris,
and I'm gonna take it.

1:40:01.625 --> 1:40:02.666
In Paris?

1:40:05.791 --> 1:40:07.833
You could come with me if you want.

1:40:14.291 --> 1:40:17.166
And what about my classes?

1:40:17.958 --> 1:40:19.583
I know, I understand.

1:40:23.708 --> 1:40:24.708
Maca…

1:40:26.583 --> 1:40:29.000
is this because of Boston?

1:40:30.583 --> 1:40:31.750
No, Leo.

1:40:33.875 --> 1:40:36.458
For the first time,
it has nothing to do with you.

1:40:47.500 --> 1:40:50.000
Something's changing in me

1:40:51.583 --> 1:40:53.958
Growing

1:40:56.041 --> 1:40:58.541
Something's changing in you

1:41:00.333 --> 1:41:02.916
It's showing

1:41:05.000 --> 1:41:07.916
I'm gonna find a light to make it bright

1:41:08.416 --> 1:41:10.625
All of these moments

1:41:13.375 --> 1:41:16.583
Leaving behind what I need to leave

1:41:17.375 --> 1:41:19.125
And continue growing

1:41:29.250 --> 1:41:33.083
You're doing a wonderful job, Luigi.
It's amazing. It's fantastic.

1:41:33.583 --> 1:41:36.833
Macarena, I didn't call you.
What are you doing here?

1:41:36.916 --> 1:41:38.291
-I'm going.
-Where?

1:41:38.375 --> 1:41:40.666
Working for you has been literal hell.

1:41:41.250 --> 1:41:44.000
You couldn't be
more cold-hearted or obnoxious.

1:41:44.083 --> 1:41:48.083
And you know what, sweetie?
You're never going to be anyone's icon.

1:41:48.166 --> 1:41:49.708
Macarena, stop.

1:41:50.208 --> 1:41:51.416
What is she doing?

1:41:55.708 --> 1:41:56.541
Cheers.

1:41:57.541 --> 1:41:58.458
You're fired.

1:41:58.541 --> 1:41:59.875
Thanks!

1:42:00.375 --> 1:42:02.958
I'm walking, consciousness, freedom

1:42:03.708 --> 1:42:08.166
I'm walking awake…

1:42:18.791 --> 1:42:19.666
Hey.

1:42:20.416 --> 1:42:22.833
I tried you both,
but neither of you picked up.

1:42:22.916 --> 1:42:24.583
Well, I know you called me before

1:42:24.666 --> 1:42:27.458
and I was the one who didn't answer,
so we're all assholes.

1:42:28.583 --> 1:42:34.875
I just… wanted to let you know
that I'm moving to Paris.

1:42:35.375 --> 1:42:36.500
For real.

1:42:37.708 --> 1:42:40.958
I got a job at a great magazine.

1:42:41.625 --> 1:42:44.583
And… I ended things with Leo.

1:42:45.625 --> 1:42:50.083
It was going well, but…
I can't think about him right now.

1:42:50.166 --> 1:42:51.833
Though I am thinking about you two.

1:42:51.916 --> 1:42:55.875
I couldn't care less if you want
to have kids or if you're necrophiliacs.

1:42:55.958 --> 1:42:57.166
I love you anyway.

1:42:57.875 --> 1:43:00.375
So, I hope you're proud of me.

1:43:00.875 --> 1:43:03.958
I made it.
I'm where I always wanted to be.

1:43:04.541 --> 1:43:08.750
And I wish… you the same,
whatever it is that you want.

1:43:19.166 --> 1:43:20.083
Hi.

1:43:21.291 --> 1:43:22.458
Come in.

1:43:22.541 --> 1:43:27.583
Remember that we're more than
the choices we make, right or wrong,

1:43:28.416 --> 1:43:30.583
and that we made it this far together.

1:43:32.125 --> 1:43:35.333
I hope I can learn to be on my own.
It doesn't scare me anymore.

1:43:36.083 --> 1:43:37.958
But I know it's gonna be hard.

1:43:38.958 --> 1:43:41.375
I know that I can call you
when I'm feeling down

1:43:41.458 --> 1:43:43.041
and that you'll visit, and…

1:43:43.875 --> 1:43:45.291
I love you so much.

1:43:47.500 --> 1:43:49.500
I miss you already.

1:44:04.208 --> 1:44:05.041
Hello.

1:44:06.583 --> 1:44:07.708
Good morning.

1:44:14.750 --> 1:44:17.791
I really feel like myself here,

1:44:18.333 --> 1:44:22.041
the way I want to be,
without caring what people think,

1:44:22.125 --> 1:44:23.958
and I'm proud of myself.

1:44:26.791 --> 1:44:29.833
WE MISS YOU!

1:44:29.916 --> 1:44:32.666
-A selfie for my Spanish friends?
-Sure.

1:44:36.791 --> 1:44:38.083
Nice.

1:44:39.041 --> 1:44:40.250
I love it.

1:44:45.625 --> 1:44:49.750
My life was missing a lot of things
when I got that job offer.

1:44:49.833 --> 1:44:53.375
But now I've embraced my past,
my present, and my future.

1:44:55.666 --> 1:44:58.125
Now I know love doesn't have to hurt.

1:45:01.000 --> 1:45:04.041
Now I know that you need to learn
to love yourself first.

1:45:05.833 --> 1:45:08.791
And only when you do that
can you really be ready to love…

1:45:10.583 --> 1:45:12.583
and share your life with someone else.

1:45:17.833 --> 1:45:18.875
Wait a minute.

1:45:18.958 --> 1:45:23.375
If this were a rom-com,
then this is how it would end.

1:45:47.666 --> 1:45:51.000
